.TH LOOTSHEET-QUEST-CREATE 1 "Mar 2026" "LootSheet" "LootSheet Manual"
.SH NAME
lootsheet-quest-create \\- Create a quest register entry
.SH SYNOPSIS
lootsheet quest create [flags]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LootSheet CLI

Usage:
  lootsheet quest create --title TEXT [--patron TEXT] [--description TEXT] [--reward AMOUNT] [--advance AMOUNT] [--bonus TEXT] [--status offered|accepted] [--accepted-on DATE]

Amounts accept D&D denominations such as 25GP, 7SP5CP, or bare CP integers.

Examples:
  lootsheet quest create --title "Goblin Bounty" --patron "Mayor Rowan" --reward 25GP
  lootsheet quest create --title "Escort the Caravan" --reward 15GP --advance 5GP --bonus "Extra 2GP if all wagons arrive intact"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
--accepted-on=string
accepted date (required if status=accepted) (default: )
.TP
--advance=string
partial advance received (default: 0)
.TP
--bonus=string
bonus conditions (default: )
.TP
--description=string
quest description (default: )
.TP
-h, --help
help for create
.TP
--patron=string
quest patron (default: )
.TP
--reward=string
promised base reward (default: 0)
.TP
--status=string
initial status (offered or accepted) (default: offered)
.TP
--title=string
quest title (required) (default: )
.SH SEE ALSO
lootsheet-quest(1)
